ter","kind":"refusal-memento","reason":"JDBC has no concept of custom collation registration at the connection level; SQLite custom collations require native callbacks not exposed through standard JDBC. Postgres supports CREATE COLLATION SQL; the mechanism diverges. Refusing rather than binding a concept the standard JDBC surface cannot express.","surface":"java.sql.Connection#setClientInfo","target_language":"java","would_close_with_cluster":"Custom collation registration on >=2 SQL drivers with structurally compatible callback semantics"},"header":{"concept":"concept:sql-collation-register","kind":"refusal-memento","surface":"java.sql.Connection#setClientInfo","targetLanguage":"java","wouldCloseWithCluster":"Custom collation registration on >=2 SQL drivers with structurally compatible callback semantics"},"schemaVersion":"1"}xŗblake3-512:415b48fe0e30bf1b1bb4e89cbc92df2d5515ad8b532f3476a14e1201548ea0750031b9ebb64d83273fa0aa9d3494dcab979e0b9c83d7a0f19467f6f4f9ba0cbbY
